#new column for total emissions by summing emissions across all sectors
df['Total'] = df.iloc[:, 1:].sum(axis=1)

#Filter out World Emissions for time-being for plotting purposes
df = df[df['Entity'] != 'World']


# Grouping the data by country and summing the emissions for each sector
grouped_df = df.groupby('Entity').sum()

# Sorting the data by total emissions in descending order
sorted_df = grouped_df.sort_values(by='Total', ascending=False)

# Selecting the top 10 countries by emissions
top_10_countries = sorted_df.iloc[:10].index.tolist()

# Selecting the top 5 emitting sectors
top_5_sectors = sorted(grouped_df.columns[:-1], key=lambda x: -grouped_df[x].sum())[:5]

# Filtering the data to only include the top 10 countries and top 5 sectors
filtered_df = df.loc[df['Entity'].isin(top_10_countries), top_5_sectors + ['Year', 'Entity']]

# Grouping the filtered data by year and country, and summing the emissions for each sector
grouped_filtered_df = filtered_df.groupby(['Year', 'Entity']).sum().reset_index()
grouped_filtered_df

# Looping through each country and creating a line chart for each sector
for country in top_10_countries:
    # Filtering the data to only include the selected country
    country_df = grouped_filtered_df[grouped_filtered_df['Entity'] == country]
    # Plotting the emissions for each sector as a line chart
    for sector in top_5_sectors:
        plt.plot(country_df['Year'], country_df[sector], label=sector)
    # Adding labels and titles to the plot
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('GHG Emissions (tCO2e)')
    plt.title(f'Emissions of Top 5 Sectors in {country} (1990-2021)')
    plt.legend()
    # Displaying the plot
    plt.show()
